Constructor Detail

IpkgBuilder

public IpkgBuilder(java.io.File dir,
                   java.lang.String path)
Construct an IpkgBuilder object with the supplied data. The created ipk file's name will be auto-generated.

Parameters:
dir - Directory of items to be added to the ipk file.
path - Filepath where the directory're contents will placed in. For example, if you want a directory to have it's contents install to "/media/cryptofs/apps/com.example.app/", then that would be the path variable.

IpkgBuilder

public IpkgBuilder(java.io.File dir,
                   java.lang.String path,
                   java.io.File ipkg)
Construct a fully populated IpkgBuilder with all required fields.

Parameters:
dir - Directory of items to be added to the ipk file.
path - Filepath where the directory're contents will placed in.
ipkg - Secified file destination for the ipk file.

setPackageID

public void setPackageID(java.lang.String id)
Sets the package ID for the resulting ipkg. IDs are unique per package on webOS devices and are created from reverse DNS naming conventions.

parseFromJsonFile

public void parseFromJsonFile(java.io.File json)
Attempts to parse a specified JSON file for package id, package name, package version, and package author. Follows the Palm webOS appinfo.json guidelines.

See Also:
Palm webOS appinfo.json

Parameters:

build

public void build()
Builds the ipk file. Any left out information will either be omitted or filled in by default values.
